name: "Unhappy Turnip" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Liner pen on notebook page with digital embellishments and color.] Grumpy. This turnip is probably still suffering from the COLLECTIVE TURNIP GESTALT memory of so many of his fellow vegetables being carved into little lanterns around this time of year for the Harvest Festival in what is NOW called the British Isles... Probably... ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
